1
00:00:09,092 --> 00:00:10,572
<i>The NBA title up for grabs</i>

2
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:12,355
<i>beginning Wednesday night
in Salt Lake City.</i>

3
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:13,471
Utah Jazz!

4
00:00:13,555 --> 00:00:16,766
<i>Part two between the defending
champs and the Mailman's crew.</i>

5
00:00:17,517 --> 00:00:19,352
<i>Super Mike and the gang looking human,</i>

6
00:00:19,436 --> 00:00:23,106
<i>working on just two days' rest
in the thin air of Salt Lake City.</i>

7
00:00:25,150 --> 00:00:27,068
After they lost
the year before...

8
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:30,155
Utah came back better the next year.

9
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:39,289
The atmosphere in Utah was, "This is it.
We can finally vanquish them."

10
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:41,708
Utah was waiting for us.

11
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:45,545
We basically had to fly
to Salt Lake the next day.

12
00:00:46,212 --> 00:00:49,424
It seemed like, uh,
we were running on fumes.

13
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:55,805
Most people struggle
to be present.

14
00:00:56,890 --> 00:01:00,810
People go and sit in ashrams for 20 years
in India trying to be present.

15
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:05,899
Do yoga, meditate,
trying to get here, now.

16
00:01:10,612 --> 00:01:12,030
What you listening to?

17
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:15,325
- What are you listening to?
- Huh?

18
00:01:15,408 --> 00:01:16,688
What are you listening to?

19
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:20,663
Kenny Lattimore.
It's brand new, not even out yet.

20
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:23,708
He's a friend of mine,
you know I can get that.

21
00:01:26,419 --> 00:01:31,299
<i>Most people live in fear because
we project the past into the future.</i>

22
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:35,553
<i>Michael's a mystic.
He was never anywhere else.</i>

23
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:38,263
Hey.

24
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:40,850
I sense you know
you're gonna win this first game.

25
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:42,870
- I sense that.
- What'd you say?

26
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:45,438
Whatever it is, it's "Yes. No. Maybe."

27
00:01:46,898 --> 00:01:50,401
Coming into the final series,
what's your mental preparation like?

28
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:53,196
Yes. No. Maybe. Whatever that was.

29
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:58,576
<i>His gift was not that he could
jump high, run fast, shoot a basketball.</i>

30
00:02:00,078 --> 00:02:02,330
- Can I walk in peace?
- Go ahead.

31
00:02:02,413 --> 00:02:03,414
I love you guys.

32
00:02:04,999 --> 00:02:08,002
<i>His gift was that
he was completely present.</i>

33
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:09,462
<i>And that was the separator.</i>

34
00:02:11,089 --> 00:02:13,091
Go ahead!

35
00:02:29,065 --> 00:02:30,650
I got up, I stretched...

36
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:32,944
had a couple beers...

37
00:02:34,404 --> 00:02:35,864
played the piano...

38
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:36,947
one cigar.

39
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:39,284
In the lobby bar?

40
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:41,411
No, in my room.

41
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:44,998
I've got a piano in my room, man.
I was in there...

42
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,916
It's called the Jordan Bar.

43
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:50,003
You see that go in?
Don't look at my fuckin' feet.

44
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:52,505
Look at where the ball is going.

45
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:56,342
MJ, you got four?

46
00:02:56,426 --> 00:02:57,552
KB's got none.

47
00:02:57,635 --> 00:02:59,596
Come on, Keith.
Get on the board, baby.

48
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:02,139
Get on the board.

49
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:05,727
Get on the board.
Go down and rebound that.

50
00:03:05,810 --> 00:03:08,104
<i>The big downfall
of a lot of players</i>

51
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:11,149
<i>who are otherwise gifted
is thinking about failure.</i>

52
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:15,987
- Goddamn it!
- Midair right there. That's like...

53
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:22,202
<i>Michael didn't allow what he
couldn't control to get inside his head.</i>

54
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:27,248
<i>He would say, "Why would I think about
missing a shot I haven't taken yet?"</i>

55
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:28,332
Garbage.

56
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,257
Goddamn!

57
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:39,636
Damn! Put 'em away, MJ.

58
00:03:45,266 --> 00:03:47,018
Ooh, I just love it!

59
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:48,894
Whoo!

60
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:53,233
<i>A spectacular move!</i>

61
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:54,901
<i>The game's over!</i>

62
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:57,320
<i>Chicago Stadium is going wild!</i>

63
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,467
<i>First of all,
there's no backstabbing going on here.</i>

64
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:02,801
<i>It's time for me to move on.</i>

65
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:05,385
<i>This will be Phil's last year
as the coach of the Bulls.</i>

66
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:10,875
- <i>Are the expectations too high?
- Where do we go from here?</i>

67
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:12,919
<i>The only question: how long can it last?</i>

68
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:27,141
<i>This year's Finals
has a familiar feel.</i>

69
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:30,561
<i>Same time, same teams,
same places, same high stakes.</i>

70
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:33,398
<i>But Utah is hoping
for a different end result this year.</i>

71
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:36,752
Remember what we said
about your breathing,

72
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:39,570
and your centering,
and getting yourself focused to the court.

73
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:43,032
You guys know that you gotta support
yourselves and your teammates.

74
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:46,286
Here in this building,
it's like sheep to the wolves.

75
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,544
In '98,
were you guys in Utah?

76
00:04:55,169 --> 00:04:57,773
- No, my mom didn't let us go.
- We were downstairs in the basement.

77
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,882
- Exactly.
- Watching the game. We had school.

78
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:03,511
She felt like Utah
was a little hostile for us as young kids.

79
00:05:09,183 --> 00:05:12,186
I don't remember much of the games,
and seeing him play.

80
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:15,982
But I remember the fans
and it was so loud.

81
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:19,944
I mean, the screaming was just nonstop.

82
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,279
It was brutal.

83
00:05:21,904 --> 00:05:23,740
We didn't like the Jazz at all.

84
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:27,118
As a family, we would get down there
and just talk so much trash.

85
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:29,120
Those games would get crazy.

86
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:33,791
<i>This Utah team is vastly
improved from last year's finalists.</i>

87
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:36,377
<i>Better skills and much more confident.</i>

88
00:05:36,461 --> 00:05:38,742
<i>The Bulls have beaten
every team this season,</i>

89
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:40,840
<i>except for the Utah Jazz.</i>

90
00:05:40,923 --> 00:05:46,763
Let's get ready to rumble!

91
00:05:47,972 --> 00:05:49,474
<i>Pippen working on Russell.</i>

92
00:05:49,557 --> 00:05:51,976
<i>Double team,
Stockton comes over and steals.</i>

93
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:55,229
<i>Stockton waltzes in
off the left side of the lane.</i>

94
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:58,358
I never said, "Oh, my goodness,
this is the Bulls."

95
00:05:58,441 --> 00:05:59,484
Great team,

96
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,570
all the respect that they deserved,
they'd get from me.

97
00:06:02,653 --> 00:06:06,866
But I sure didn't feel an aura
about Michael Jordan or the Bulls.

98
00:06:06,949 --> 00:06:10,912
I don't know how you would play against
somebody with that. We were there to win.

99
00:06:10,995 --> 00:06:12,789
<i>Kukoc has it picked off
by Russell,</i>

100
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,832
<i>handed to Stockton, now Malone!</i>

101
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:20,129
<i>Twenty-second timeout, Chicago!</i>

102
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:26,719
Guys, this is a scary fucking situation.
This game should be dead fucking meat.

103
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:29,639
Now, goddamn it,
get yourselves serious on this.

104
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:32,058
Come on, think positive, man.
Let's go.

105
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:34,894
<i>It's Scottie back to Michael.
Russell's on him.</i>

106
00:06:34,977 --> 00:06:38,564
<i>Around the Longley screen.
Michael... dishes to Longley.</i>

107
00:06:39,107 --> 00:06:40,983
<i>Up with the shot... to tie the game!</i>

108
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:44,529
<i>And it's overtime in game one.</i>

109
00:06:46,864 --> 00:06:47,990
Come on now, let's go.

110
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:52,120
<i>Twenty-one for Malone!
Hooked away by Hornacek!</i>

111
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:53,538
<i>Trying to stop him.</i>

112
00:06:53,621 --> 00:06:56,124
<i>He's chased by Jordan,
but makes it in anyway!</i>

113
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:06,926
<i>And game one goes to Utah in overtime.</i>

114
00:07:10,555 --> 00:07:12,390
Knowing that this
is the last dance,

115
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:15,143
I'm trying to muster up
the energy to finish this off.

116
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:17,979
We were mentally, physically exhausted,

117
00:07:18,062 --> 00:07:21,357
but we didn't lose focus
on what we were trying to achieve.

118
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:25,486
<i>Hornacek on Michael, fadeaway...</i>

119
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:26,945
<i>Got it!</i>

120
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:30,450
<i>Pippen slices through the defense
and slams it.</i>

121
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:33,786
<i>Kukoc... hits off the baseline.</i>

122
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:38,082
<i>Michael, with the shot clock winding down,
against Hornacek.</i>

123
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,793
<i>Michael's gonna do it.
Two defenders, a whistle...</i>

124
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:44,046
<i>Count the basket, plus the foul.</i>

125
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:49,677
<i>Chicago comes into Salt Lake City,
weary or not, and gets out with a split.</i>

126
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,345
Three more, three more.

127
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:55,349
They swept LA.

128
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:58,811
You know how much it takes to guard Shaq
and try to push that motherfucker around?

129
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:00,771
That ain't the point. I ain't Shaq.

130
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:02,607
- Huh?
- I ain't Shaq.

131
00:08:03,774 --> 00:08:05,568
Like I said, I ain't Shaq.

132
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,906
The Jazz won game one
in overtime at home.

133
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:11,991
The Bulls won a close game to even it.

134
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:13,784
It was a hard-fought series...

135
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:16,287
except for game three in Chicago.

136
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:18,122
<i>♪ Right here! Right now! ♪</i>

137
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:20,666
<i>♪ Right here! Right now!
Right here! ♪</i>

138
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,377
Gentlemen, game three!
Have a great game.

139
00:08:23,461 --> 00:08:24,461
Careful.

140
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:28,966
<i>Here's Scottie, into the lane,
another runner.</i>

141
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,260
<i>He hits it, plus he's coming to the line.</i>

142
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:34,096
<i>Eisley has it blocked by Harper.</i>

143
00:08:35,014 --> 00:08:37,183
<i>Karl on the run, a hook. It's an airball.</i>

144
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:42,396
<i>Michael spins on Hornacek
to the left hand. An absolute beauty.</i>

145
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:02,917
<i>Somehow, someway... he scores.</i>

146
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:09,173
The Utah Jazz of Malone and Stockton,

147
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:12,343
the Jazz who managed to get to the Finals
two years in a row,

148
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:14,512
were held to 54 points.

149
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:19,559
The lowest point total since the advent
of the shot clock in any game,

150
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:21,018
not just a playoff game.

151
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:22,811
Ridiculous.

152
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:25,439
Now Bill's the only one who ain't scored.

153
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:28,526
<i>Wennington,
the only Bull who hasn't scored.</i>

154
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:29,777
<i>So let him do it.</i>

155
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:33,281
<i>Well, the evening is complete!</i>

156
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:38,661
<i>A total humiliation for the Utah Jazz.</i>

157
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:40,246
<i>Beaten by 42.</i>

158
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:47,003
<i>Chicago leads the series two games to one,
but somehow it seems like more than that.</i>

159
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:50,673
- Coach...
- This is actually the score?

160
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,261
- Is this the final?
- That's the final.

161
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:09,817
In sports, Dennis Rodman
is in more hot water this morning.

162
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,569
<i>The talk at practice Monday</i>

163
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:14,614
<i>wasn't just about what the Jazz
was missing in game three,</i>

164
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:17,366
<i>but who the Bulls were missing
the day after.</i>

165
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:21,203
<i>Dennis Rodman, once again,
was nowhere to be found.</i>

166
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:23,599
Is it true that Dennis
wasn't at practice today?

167
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,559
- That's true.
- Is that an excused absence?

168
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:28,002
- No, it's not.
- What transpired?

169
00:10:28,669 --> 00:10:30,087
I don't know. He's not here.

170
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:37,470
I got the world heavyweight title,
and with Rodzilla in the house,

171
00:10:37,553 --> 00:10:42,975
there will be no stopping
nWo Hollywood now!

172
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:45,686
So, Dennis Rodman
ran off after game three.

173
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:48,022
He took a detour, um,

174
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:50,191
from playing with the Bulls

175
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:52,902
to become a wrestler with Hulk Hogan.

176
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:57,990
And by the way, big dog,
I just love the way

177
00:10:58,074 --> 00:11:01,285
you threw Malone around like a dishrag.

178
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:04,121
You just be the bomb, brah.

179
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:06,791
I wasn't trying anything.

180
00:11:06,874 --> 00:11:10,211
I was just trying to play basketball,
party... fuck all the girls.

181
00:11:10,294 --> 00:11:13,464
And so that just happened to be me,
Dennis shit, you know.

182
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:17,051
There are some things
worth missing practice for, brother.

183
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:22,682
He has a chartered plane ready and waiting
to whisk him off to some wrestling deal

184
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:26,102
where the scripted action called for him
to hit a guy with a chair.

185
00:11:27,645 --> 00:11:29,814
<i>Oh, my goodness!
That was Rodman!</i>

186
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:34,026
Dennis' sideshow,
is it a reality check for the Bulls?

187
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:37,321
I think they're all very disturbed,
the coaches and the players.

188
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:39,949
<i>He'll be fined
for this latest offense.</i>

189
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:42,576
Rodman faces punishment by the Bulls
for missing practice.

190
00:11:51,335 --> 00:11:53,563
Dickey, you weren't here
at the start were you?

191
00:11:53,587 --> 00:11:54,587
No.

192
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:58,300
We beat up Dennis with some boffers.
You got to miss out on that shit.

193
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:03,597
Because he brought fame
and disreputation on all of us.

194
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:05,474
We were dishonored.

195
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:07,643
That's a good piece of money,
though.

196
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:11,095
All right, let's go.

197
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:15,025
Come on, Rodzilla! Rodzilla!

198
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:20,281
The bad-boy reputation that, frankly,
Dennis carefully cultivated

199
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:22,616
overshadowed his contributions
as a player.

200
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:27,204
But Phil knew
that he was a singular defensive player

201
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:32,418
who contributed mightily
to the success of that team.

202
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:36,005
Does it bother you that he's
taking away the focus from the Finals?

203
00:12:36,088 --> 00:12:39,258
No, he's only taking your focus
away from the Finals, not ours.

204
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:44,388
I just think that Phil realized
that I need to always do me,

205
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:45,723
just go do what I do.

206
00:12:45,806 --> 00:12:48,726
You know, like the playoff game,
I went to go wrestle.

207
00:12:48,809 --> 00:12:51,937
If I did this, I go over here,
if I do that, I got to go do this.

208
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:54,064
They're gonna get 100%
when I'm on the court.

209
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:57,007
If they see him, they'll think
he'll go out that way.

210
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,695
If he closes the door, they just think...

211
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:00,779
Here's the problem.

212
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:03,699
You got 300 freaking media out there.

213
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:07,495
Dennis blew off practice and he got fined
and he's got nothing to say to nobody.

214
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:09,288
As he would say, "in his words."

215
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:12,917
So we gotta try to sneak him out
gate three and a half...

216
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:16,629
while 300 media are in the main hallway
in front of the locker room.

217
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:18,339
I don't know if we'll get that done.

218
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,807
<i>Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.</i>

219
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:12,852
<i>Has there been a Rodman sighting or is he
off wrestling with Hulk Hogan tonight?</i>

220
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:15,437
<i>Eisley, gotta get rid of it.</i>

221
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:19,817
<i>Rebound to Rodman.
It's a two-point game...</i>

222
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:23,696
<i>and it stays there as Pippen misses,
but Rodman chases it down.</i>

223
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:27,199
<i>Rodman is there!</i>

224
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:28,868
<i>Scottie for three!</i>

225
00:14:30,911 --> 00:14:33,414
<i>Rodman's there and Anderson fouled him.</i>

226
00:14:34,498 --> 00:14:36,417
<i>The Worm is a poor free throw shooter.</i>

227
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:40,671
<i>Certainly not the guy you want on the line
in this situation if you're Phil Jackson.</i>

228
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:45,050
